The upstream project README describes AI Berkshire as an investment research Skill collection compatible with Claude Code and Codex, systematizing value-investing methods through AI Agent workflows.

Meridian Research Engine 2.0 is a derivative and substantially reorganized project focused on macro-cycle analysis, sector rotation, data audit, report gatekeeping, price-level mapping, portfolio-execution checks, and conservative research workflow discipline.

Modification summary
--------------------

Compared with the upstream AI Berkshire project, this repository has been adapted and extended toward:

- Meridian Research Engine 2.0 naming and repository identity;
- macro-cycle and sector-rotation workflow;
- six-factor macro scoring;
- market-pricing and consensus-validation checks;
- data reliability and data meaning rules;
- Price Level Engine / 点位精算引擎;
- portfolio cost and execution checks;
- report gatekeeper requirements;
- generic public examples using SAMPLE / TICKER placeholders;
- additional tests and GitHub Actions workflow.

